     <h2><font color="#000080"><!-- 2004-09-02 -->
	 
	 Malcolm Gladwell: Story Teller
	 </font>
     </h2>
    

	<p>
    <div style="clear:both;"></div><p>Here's more from the person that is becoming my favorite story teller.&nbsp; I'll bet opinions about this particular topic and Gladwell's conclusion are all over the map.</p> <div class="wlWriterSmartContent" id="0767317B-992E-4b12-91E0-4F059A8CECA8:6d2983f0-df7b-4369-8fe5-8d38c22f8565" contenteditable="false" style="padding-right: 0px; display: inline; padding-left: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; margin: 0px; padding-top: 0px">Technorati Tags: <a href="http://technorati.com/tags/orcmid" rel="tag">orcmid</a>, <a href="http://technorati.com/tags/Malcolm%20Gladwell" rel="tag">Malcolm Gladwell</a>, <a href="http://technorati.com/tags/genius" rel="tag">genius</a>, <a href="http://technorati.com/tags/video%20notes" rel="tag">video notes</a>, <a href="http://technorati.com/tags/Microsoft%20Soapbox" rel="tag">Microsoft Soapbox</a></div> <p><a title="The New Yorker Conference, 2012: Stories from the Near Future, Malcolm Gladwell" href="http://soapbox.msn.com/video.aspx?vid=a964171d-4d95-4e14-af2b-607cbddb1fda" target="_new"><img height="84" alt="The New Yorker Conference, 2012: Stories from the Near Future, Malcolm Gladwell" src="http://a1813.g.akamai.net/f/1813/23830/v0001/msnuuv1.download.akamai.com/23830/thumbs/prod/7c/30/7f/2f20df9b-f8e3-47e3-8549-648ce37f307c.jpg" width="112" border="0"><br>The New Yorker Conference, 2012: Stories from the Near Future, Malcolm Gladwell</a> </p> <p>My attention is on Gladwell as a storyteller.&nbsp; I don't know whether he spent 10,000 hours practicing story-telling in person, or whether all of his time as a writer counts toward his on-stage story telling.&nbsp; Watch the 27-minute video to see what I am talking about.</p> <hr> <small> <p>I ran into this video because I am uploading my first two video notes to Microsoft Soapbox.&nbsp; Soapbox takes freakin' forever to process videos before they become available for video.&nbsp; The post-processing-massaging-transcoding-whatever takes longer than the uploads which take almost as long as it takes to store the single, large Windows Media Video files out of Windows Movie Editor.&nbsp; So, while I was cracking peanut shells and drumming my fingers on my desk, I watch this video that showed up as popular on Soapbox.&nbsp; One of mine is now ready for viewing (after almost 3 hours), so I will now, as is completely predictable for me, <a href="http://soapbox.msn.com/video.aspx?vid=c5fbbd78-7ebe-4b81-875a-7bca8936f7d2">go review it</a>.</p></small><div style="clear:both; padding-bottom:0.25em"></div>
    </p>
	<span class="byline">posted by orcmid 
       at <a href="http://orcmid.com/blog/2007/06/malcolm-gladwell-story-teller.asp">6/29/2007 03:23:00 PM</a></span>
	  
         <!-- 2004-05-10 -->
